A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 12 of Title 19 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to name
2 changes, so as to provide for the sealing of name change petitions upon request; to provide
3 for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
5 SECTION 1.
6 Chapter 12 of Title 19 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to name changes,
7 is amended by revising subsections (a) and (c) of Code Section 19-12-1, relating to petition
8 for name change, request by victim of family violence or human trafficking, notice of filing,
9 and consent of minor's parents or guardian, as follows:
10 "(a) As used in this Code section, the term:
11 (1) 'Abandoned' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code Section 15-11-2.
12 (2) 'Child' means an unemancipated individual who is under 18 years of age.
13 (3) 'Family violence' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code Section 19-13-1.
14 (4) 'Human trafficking' means an offense provided for under Code Section 16-5-46."
