15 "(c)(1) When a name change is requested by a petitioner who alleges to be a victim of
16 family violence or human trafficking, such petitioner may petition the court to file his or
17 her petition to change his or her name under seal.
18 (2) If the court determines that the petitioner is a victim of family violence or human
19 trafficking authorizes that such petition be kept under seal, the court may issue an order
20 waiving the requirements of publication as set forth in subsection (d) of this Code section.
21 If the court determines that such filing shall be allowed to proceed under seal and
22 otherwise waives the other requirements of this Code section, it may hear and determine
23 all of the matters raised in such petition and render a final judgment thereon.
24 (3) After issuing an order under paragraph (2) of this subsection, the court may later
25 unseal a petition for name change or order the petitioner to file a redacted version of such
26 petition for the public record.
27 (4) If the court determines that the petitioner is not a victim of family violence or human
28 trafficking, the The underlying petition for name change shall not be heard until this Code
29 section has been complied with in full.
30 (5) The court shall retain all filings made under seal as part of the record."
31 SECTION 2.
32 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
